---
description: "Rules for importing UI designs into Roblox Studio (shell-first, no logic)"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Import Assumptions

UI imports are based on:
- image exports (PNG preferred)
- one screen/container per export

Do NOT assume MCP or semantic layout data.

---

## Shell-First Construction (MANDATORY)

When importing UI:
- build instance hierarchy ONLY
- create Frames, ImageLabels, ImageButtons, TextLabels
- apply layout, sizing, constraints, and names

Automation must NOT:
- invent logic
- invent states
- wire gameplay
- add networking or persistence

---

## Scaling & Layout Rules

Defaults:
- Prefer SCALE over OFFSET
- Use OFFSET only for fixed-size icons, borders, or text clarity
- ScaleType = Fit unless element is a stretch/fill bar
- AnchorPoint = 0.5, 0.5 for animated/selectable elements

AspectRatioConstraint:
- Allowed ONLY on Menu Container (TYPE 2)
- Do NOT scatter constraints across children

Scrolling:
- Only Menu Content may scroll
- ScrollingDirection = Y unless explicitly required
- AutomaticCanvasSize = Y

Glows inside scroll areas must live INSIDE their cell and be clipped by it.

---

## Asset Rules

- Prefer grayscale assets
- Apply color via ImageColor3 / UIGradient
- Do NOT bake dynamic text into images

Dynamic text includes:
prices, timers, counts, labels, stats
